item.p:
Minimum total Capital Adequacy Ratio (CAR):
                  11.5% of risk-weighted assets, inclusive of the
                  capital conservation buffer of 2.5%;

issue directives to any banking company to take such action as the State Bank
                  considers necessary in the interests of depositors, the banking company, or the
                  banking system as a whole;

remove from office any director, chief executive, or officer of a banking
                  company who is found to be not fit and proper, or who has acted in a manner
                  prejudicial to the interests of the banking company or its depositors;

Nationwide microfinance bank (operating in more than one province or federal
                  territory): PKR 1,000,000,000 (one billion
                  Pakistani Rupees);

Province-wide microfinance bank (operating within a single province):
                  PKR 500,000,000 (five hundred million Pakistani
                  Rupees);

General micro credit: maximum loan size
                  PKR 500,000 (five hundred thousand Pakistani
                  Rupees) per individual borrower;

Micro enterprise loan: maximum loan size
                  PKR 3,000,000 (three million Pakistani
                  Rupees) per borrower;

Housing microfinance: maximum loan size
                  PKR 3,000,000 (three million Pakistani Rupees)
                  per borrower;

a transfer order entered into a designated payment system prior to the
                  commencement of insolvency proceedings shall not be affected by such
                  proceedings;

the designated payment system shall be entitled to net any obligations of the
                  insolvent participant against funds or securities held by or due to such
                  participant;

Maximum per-transaction amount:
                  PKR 50,000 (fifty thousand Pakistani
                  Rupees);

Maximum daily aggregate amount:
                  PKR 200,000 (two hundred thousand Pakistani
                  Rupees);

pacs.008 — FIToFICustomerCreditTransfer:
                  used for all payment initiation messages from the debtor institution to the
                  creditor institution;

pacs.002 —
                  FIToFIPaymentStatusReport: used for all payment status responses from the
                  creditor institution to the debtor institution;

Full EMI licence: authorizing the issuance of e-money, operation of e-money
                  wallets, cash-in and cash-out services through agents, and inter-wallet and
                  bank-to-wallet transfers;

The EMI shall maintain a comprehensive agent management system with real-time
                  monitoring of agent activity, including flagging of unusual transaction
                  patterns;

The trust account balance shall at all times equal or exceed
                  100% of the total outstanding e-money
                  liabilities;

Trust account funds shall be invested only in liquid assets, including
                  Government of Pakistan Treasury Bills, balances with SBP, or balances with
                  scheduled commercial banks;

A civil penalty not exceeding three times the amount involved in the
                  contravention, or PKR 5,000,000 (five
                  million Pakistani Rupees), whichever is greater;

In the case of a continuing contravention, an additional penalty not exceeding
                  PKR 100,000 (one hundred thousand
                  Pakistani Rupees) for each day during which the contravention continues;
